ank9      = 4\n| CONviewers9  = {{#expr:6.71-4.60}}<!--Listed as expression, calculated per WP:CALC-->\n| CONrank9     = 9\n| total9       = 6.71\n| auxC9        = 85\n| ref9         = <ref name=\"AllRatings\" /><ref name=\"BARB\" /><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.doctorwhonews.net/2014/10/flatline-overnight-viewing-figures.html |title=Flatline - Overnight Viewing Figures |work=Doctor Who News |date=19 October 2014 |accessdate=25 October 2018}}</ref>\n\n| title10      = [[#ep251|In the Forest of the Night]]\n| date10       = 25 October 2014\n| OVviewers10  = 5.03\n| OVrank10     = 3\n| CONviewers10 = {{#expr:6.92-5.03}}<!--Listed as expression, calculated per WP:CALC-->\n| CONrank10    = 7\n| total10      = 6.92\n| auxC10       = 83\n| ref10        = <ref name=\"AllRatings\" /><ref name=\"BARB\" /><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.doctorwhonews.net/2014/10/in-forest-of-night-overnight-viewing.html |title=In the Forest of the Night - Overnight Viewing Figures |work=Doctor Who News |date=26 October 2014 |accessdate=25 October 2018}}</ref>\n\n| title11      = [[#ep252a|Dark Water]]\n| date11       = 1 November 2014\n| OVviewers11  = 5.27\n| OVrank11     = 4\n| CONviewers11 = {{#expr:7.34-5.27}}<!--Listed as expression, calculated per WP:CALC-->\n| CONrank11    = 7\n| total11      = 7.34\n| auxC11       = 85\n| ref11        = <ref name=\"AllRatings\" /><ref name=\"BARB\" /><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.doctorwhonews.net/2014/11/dark-water-overnight-viewing-figures.html |title=Dark Water - Overnight Viewing Figures |work=Doctor Who News |date=2 November 2014 |accessdate=25 October 2018}}</ref>\n\n| title12      = [[#ep252b|Death in Heaven]]\n| date12       = 8 November 2014\n| OVviewers12  = 5.45\n| OVrank12     = 3\n| CONviewers12 = {{#expr:7.60-5.45}}<!--Listed as expression, calculated per WP:CALC-->\n| CONrank12    = 6\n| total12      = 7.60\n| auxC12       = 83\n| ref12        = <ref name=\"AllRatings\" /><ref name=\"BARB\">{{cite web|url=http://www.barb.co.uk/whats-new/weekly-top-30 |title=Weekly top 30 programmes |publisher=[[Broadcasters' Audience Research Board]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.doctorwhonews.net/2014/11/death-in-heaven-overnight-viewing.html |title=Death in Heaven - Overnight Viewing Figures |work=Doctor Who News |date=9 November 2014 |accessdate=25 October 2018}}</ref>\n}}\n\n===Critical reception===\n<!--DO NOT INCLUDE POORLY SOURCED INFORMATION ON FAN RECEPTION, AND DO NOT EDIT WAR.-->\nCritical reaction to series 8 was highly positive, with many labelling it a return to form and one of ''Doctor Who''{{'s}} strongest seasons.<ref name=\"avclub.com\">{{cite web|url=http://www.avclub.com/tvclub/doctor-who-kill-moon-210100|title=Review: Doctor Who: \"Kill The Moon\" \u00b7 TV Club \u00b7 The A.V. Club|publisher=}}</ref><ref name=\"Den of Geek\">{{cite web|url=http://www.denofgeek.com/tv/doctor-who/32273/doctor-who-series-8-the-caretaker-review|title=Doctor Who series 8: The Caretaker review|work=Den of Geek}}</ref><ref name=\"dvdtalk.com\">{{cite web|url=http://www.dvdtalk.com/reviews/65502/doctor-who-season-8/|title=Doctor Who: Season 8 (Blu-ray)|work=DVD Talk|accessdate=1 January 2015}}</ref> On [[Rotten Tomatoes]], the series holds an approval rating of 92%, based on 24 reviews, and an average score of 8.17/10, with the website's critics consensus stating that \"Like a TARDIS dropping down in a burst of excitement, Peter Capaldi adds a revitalizing blast of boldness and humor to ''Doctor Who''{{'}}s time-tested formula.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/doctor_who/s08|title=Doctor Who: Season 8|website=Rotten Tomatoes|access-date=6 December 2018}}</ref> [[Metacritic]] gave the series a weighted average score of 80/100, signifying \"generally favourable reviews\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.metacritic.com/tv/doctor-who/season-8|title=Doctor Who \u2013 Season 8 Reviews \u2013 Metacritic|publisher=}}</ref> Ian Jane of ''[[DVD Talk]]'' gave the series 4.5 out of 5, calling it an improvement over the Matt Smith years, praising Capaldi's performance for \"[breathing] new life to the show\", Clara's character development and the writing, and found the series' flaws not to overshadow its overall quality.<ref name=\"dvdtalk.com\"/> Many critics gave favourable praise towards the show's renewed focus on character development and the darker tone of the stories,<ref name=\"Den of Geek\"/> yet the ''[[Radio Times]]'' reported that the latter element drew a degree of controversy after it received criticism from parents of young children.<ref>{{cite web|title=Doctor Who: BBC defends afterlife cremation scene in series finale after viewers complain|url=http://www.radiotimes.com/news/2014-11-06/doctor-who-bbc-defends-afterlife-cremation-scene-in-series-finale-after-viewers-complain|publisher=[[Radio Times]]|date=6 November 2014}}</ref>\n\nCritical reception to individual episodes was predominantly positive, with \"Listen\" and \"Dark Water\" receiving critical acclaim after many critics noted them as potential classics and some of ''Doctor Who''{{'s}} finest episodes.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.avclub.com/tvclub/doctor-who-listen-209034|title=Review: Doctor Who: \"Listen\" \u00b7 TV Club \u00b7 The A.V. Club|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/tv/reviews/doctor-who-listen-review-possibly-steven-moffats-most-terrifying-episode-to-date-9722321.html|title=Doctor Who, Listen, review: Possibly Steven Moffat's most terrifying episode|work=The Independent}}</ref> \"Deep Breath\", \"Into the Dalek\", \"Time Heist\", \"[[The Caretaker (Doctor Who)|The Caretaker]]\",  \"[[Flatline (Doctor Who)|Flatline]]\" and \"Death in Heaven\" also received predominantly positive reviews from critics.<ref name=\"Den of Geek\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.avclub.com/tvclub/doctor-who-caretaker-209787|title=Review: Doctor Who: \"The Caretaker\" \u00b7 TV Club \u00b7 The A.V. Club|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/tv/reviews/doctor-who-into-the-dalek-review-a-classic-scifi-adventure-with-all-the-spectacle-of-a-blockbuster-9694979.html|title=Doctor Who, Into the Dalek, TV review: Classic sci-fi adventure has blockbuster spectacle|work=The Independent}}</ref> \"[[Kill the Moon]]\" widely divided critics after its broadcast - some praised it as a classic matching that of \"Listen\",<ref name=\"avclub.com\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/tvandradio/doctor-who/11138801/Doctor-Who-Kill-The-Moon-review-terrifying-touching.html|title=Doctor Who, Kill The Moon, review: 'terrifying, touching'|author=Ben Lawrence|date=4 October 2014|work=Telegraph.co.uk}}</ref> while others found it as a weak or badly-scripted episode.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/tv/reviews/doctor-who-series-8-kill-the-moon-bbc1--tv-review-perhaps-the-weakest-episode-so-far-this-series-9776006.html|title=Doctor Who series 8, Kill the Moon \u2013 review: The weakest episode so far this series|work=The Independent}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/ewanspence/2014/10/04/doctor-who-series-8-episode-7-review-kill-the-moon/|title=Doctor Who Series 8 Episode 7 Review: Kill The Moon|author=Ewan Spence|date=4 October 2014|work=Forbes}}</ref> Dan Martin, writing for ''The Guardian'', criticised \"[[Mummy on the Orient Express]]\"; despite other critics giving the episode positive reviews, his focus was on the display of \"sexual tension\" between the Doctor and Clara that went against views by the show's cast, who previously stated that there would be no flirting between the two.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/tvandradioblog/2014/oct/11/doctor-who-recap-series-34-episode-eight-mummy-on-the-orient-express|title=Doctor Who recap: series 34, episode eight \u2013 Mummy on the Orient Express|author=Dan Martin|work=the Guardian}}</ref>\n\n===Awards and nominations===\n{{See 